#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code har element of nums1 ke liye nums2 me uska Next Greater Element nikal raha hai.

1. nextGreat() function nums2 par right se left traverse karta hai.
2. Monotonic decreasing stack use hota hai:
   - current se chhote ya equal elements pop kar do
   - jo top bachega wahi next greater hoga
3. Har element ka NGE ek HashMap me store kar diya jata hai.
4. Fir target element ka answer map se return kar diya jata hai.
5. Main function me nums1 ke har element ke liye nextGreat() call karke ans array fill kar diya gaya hai.

Main idea:
nums2 ke elements ka NGE stack se efficiently nikala ja raha hai,
aur map me store karke target ka answer liya ja raha hai.

Important point:
Is code me problem ye hai ki har nums1[i] ke liye nextGreat() dobara poora nums2 traverse kar raha hai.
Matlab same NGE map baar-baar ban raha hai.

Time Complexity of this code: O(nums1.length * nums2.length)
Space Complexity: O(nums2.length)

Better idea:
Ek baar nums2 ka pura NGE map bana lo, fir nums1 ke sab answers O(1) lookup se nikaal lo.

#Code:

class Solution {

    private int nextGreat(int[] nums2, int target){
        Deque<Integer> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();
        HashMap<Integer, Integer> ngeMap = new HashMap<>();
        //Step-1: Find NGE for all the elements
        for(int i=nums2.length-1; i>=0; i--){
            while(!stack.isEmpty() && stack.peek() <= nums2[i]){
                stack.pop();
            }

            if(stack.isEmpty()){
                ngeMap.put(nums2[i], -1);
            }else{
                ngeMap.put(nums2[i], stack.peek());
            }
            stack.push(nums2[i]);
        }
        int ans = ngeMap.get(target);
        return ans;

    }

    public int[] nextGreaterElement(int[] nums1, int[] nums2) {
        int[] ans = new int[nums1.length];

        //Step-1: sbhi elements mei ghumenge and unke next greater nikalkr current element ka check krenge
        for(int i=0; i<nums1.length; i++){
            int result = nextGreat(nums2, nums1[i]);
            ans[i] = result;
        }

        return ans;
    }
}
